cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with multi-person tracking using appearance modeling. The paper also involves machine learning techniques for feature selection and incremental learning, which makes it likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of mid-level semantic features and the evaluation of the model on a benchmark dataset suggests that it could also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the incorporation of the model into an online tracking-by-detection framework makes it relevant to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
